# Internationalization (i18n) Guidelines

## Translation System

### i18n Utilities
- [i18n.ts](mdc:src/utils/i18n.ts) - Core internationalization utilities
- Use translation keys instead of hardcoded strings
- Support multiple languages through translation tables
- Handle fallback gracefully

### Usage in Components
```tsx
import { t } from '../utils/i18n'

// Later in the component
<button title={t('importFiles', language)}>
  <Plus size={16} />
</button>
```

## Language Support

### Currently Supported Languages
- Chinese (zh) - Primary language
- English (en) - Alternative language

### Text Guidelines
- Keep UI text concise and clear
- Use consistent terminology across the application
- Maintain proper text alignment for different languages
- Use proper locale-specific formatting for dates, numbers, etc.

## UI Considerations

### Layout Adaptations
- Design UI to accommodate text expansion/contraction
- Use flexible layouts that adapt to content length
- Avoid fixed-width containers for text
- Test UI with all supported languages

### Special Characters
- Ensure proper rendering of special characters
- Use Unicode-compatible fonts
- Handle RTL languages properly if supported

## Feature Naming

### Consistent Terminology
- Use standardized translations for feature names:
  - "视频理解" (Video Understanding)
  - "导出" (Export)
  - "时间线" (Timeline)
- Maintain consistent terminology in UI, documentation, and logs